attributes.about_this_biz_history: Here in the small and cozy town of Mission BC homes a unique restaurant called Embers BBQ House. This charming little hole in the wall is situated on the North bank of the Fraser River overlooking the Central Fraser Valley eighty kilometres east of Vancouver. Embers BBQ House has been a family owned and operated restaurant for the past 15 years. Embers prides itself on serving spectacular authentic BBQ that has been recruiting loyal customers since it's small beginnings. The restaurant has a vibrant and open kitchen and dinning concept. This creates for a unique and enjoyable dinning atmosphere that will not only provide a delicious meal but a show. Embers heart and soul is their food.The chefs take pride in their full homemade menu that will please anyone's taste buds. The cuisine is down right comfort food that will warm you're belly and your soul. Embers offers a variety of favourites dishes.

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
You'll find The Mission Springs Pub & Restaurant absolutely fascinating.  It's busting with collectibles, antiques, and memorabilia aplenty to satisfy curious minds.  Old signs and furnishings embellish the walls.  Much of the memorabilia on the pub walls is local and local residents did most of the decorating. It reflects our "the times are changin'" motif. 

Our made-from-scratch kitchen offers fresh-baked bread to homemade sauces and has established our reputation for pub food with a flair.  The portions suit real appetites, while the prices remain fair, at from $8 to $12 per plate.

Customers have been enjoying large-portioned, home-cooked food and frosty cold ones for the past 20 years while dancing through the night in our 120-seat pub.  Our DJs are more than happy to play your requests while you enjoy a dance and our fine ales.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio: Betty is as much a Mission icon as Rockos Diner. Betty has been manager for many years and has served generations of Rockos diners. Betty was a former roller girl server back in the day. No longer sporting rollerskates, but always quick with a comment, Betty is a Rockos treasure.
attributes.about_this_biz_history: Rockos started out as a roadside diner on the outskirts of Mission BC. Originally called Nicks DIner it boosted a paved parking lot and became a popular hang out for car buffs, due to the Mission Raceway. It was purchased by the Schiller family in 1985 and is still family owned and operated by the Schilers. Rockos has been 24 hours for as long as anyone can remember. Rockos 50's flare and original structure has made it a popular location for the film industry as a site location. .
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Open 24 hours Rockos serves breakfast ANYTIME!! We are know for our huge helpings pleasant wait staff and casual comfortable atmosphere. One of the last free standing independently owned traditional diners Rockos has been in Mission for 55 years. We still have some of the original classic items including the footlong hotdog, patty melt and the hi-light combo burger complete with a wiener. Milkshakes are a favorite at Rockos with over 20 flavors to chose from. Whether it be one of our colossal size burgers, homemade meatloaf dinner,  or a stack of hotcakes, . Join us anytime - we are always open

attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Cedar Ridge Golf Course & Driving Range offers an excellent golf experience by providing guests with an 18-hole Par 3 golf course that can be enjoyed in less time than a full size course - while still providing challenges to the practiced golfer and attainable successes to the beginner. The log-constructed driving range with heated stalls allows for year-round comfort. The 26.5 acres of well-maintained greens and mature landscape is set against the beautiful backdrop of the Cedar Valley in the Fraser Valley. A sandy soil base allows for early and late season golfing opportunities. Cedar Ridge is also the only complete Practice Facility in Mission. The walk along Cedar Ridge offers a scenic view of the mountains, gorgeous tree-lined fairways as well as water hazards and sand traps. Cedar Ridge will offer the 9 to 5'er a place to play, particularly after work when guests have only a couple of hours of daylight. Most importantly, Cedar Ridge will offer an affordable golf experience.

attributes.about_this_biz_history: In 1958, two brothers borrowed $600 from their mom to open a pizza place in Wichita, Kansas. They named it Pizza Hut because their sign only had room for eight letters. How profound! Soon, the restaurant grew. Why? The pizza was awesome. The service felt like home. And the customers were treated like family. And we've been delivering that same food and service ever since. For the Love of Pizza Since 1958. From day one, the Carney brothers could look their customers in the eye and promise them the finest pizza in town -- because they knew the farmers who grew the ingredients, and they knew those farmers cared about quality. Since then, our farmers have grown right alongside us, and the ingredients we use are still our highest priority. No one loves pizza more than Pizza Hut. That's why pizza is in our name -- and always will be.
